  abstract={In this paper, we study the No-wait Drone Scheduling Traveling Salesman Problem (NW-DSTSP) based on Hybrid Adaptive Particle Swarm Optimization-Genetic Algorithm (HAPGA). It is supposed that a truck sets out from a depot with some drones, and they need to arrive at several clustered customer locations. The NW-DSTSP seeks for a dynamic route of the truck and drones where all customer needs are met with minimal makespan (or operating costs). We construct a three-step solution to formulate NW-DSTSP as a Mixed Integer Linear Program (MILP) and propose the HAPGA to obtain solutions for small and medium-sized instances. The model is compared with the K-means clustering and TSP models, while HAPGA is compared with PSO and GA. The results show that the model and algorithm we proposed are more effective.},
