  pages={352-355},
  abstract={Autonomous cooperative decision control of UAV cluster is a high integration of intelligent control technology and platform control technology. It is the technical basis of intelligent UAV cluster cooperative operation. UAVs with autonomous control ability can achieve a high degree of autonomous cooperation through organizational rules and information interaction. In the complex dynamic environment and time sensitive situation, it can quickly and effectively obtain, process and transmit various information and control multiple platforms. This paper mainly focuses on the cooperative control of intelligent multi UAV systems, focusing on the key technical problems such as the cooperative control architecture of multi UAV systems in complex battlefield environment, dynamic cooperative task allocation, online cooperative path planning. The multi-UAV cooperative track planning algorithm Mcppbev with extended voronoi diagram is used to simulate, and the coordinated trajectory planning of multiple UAVs and targets is simulated and studied, and the simulation results are verified to verify the effectiveness and real-time performance of the algorithm.},
